  "learn": {
    "heading": "Making ratios comparable",
    "intro": "<p>To compare ratios, scale them so one part matches — then compare the other part. It's just like making a <strong>common denominator</strong> to compare fractions.</p>",
    "examples": [
      "Compare 1:2 and 2:3. Scale to a common first part: 1:2 → 2:4. Now 2:4 vs 2:3 — same first part, so the smaller second part (3) is the <em>stronger</em> ratio.",
      "Bigger second number per same first number means more of that part — same as 2/4 vs 2/3."
    ]
